{"type":"message","id":"76672c6b","parentId":"f65f347d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:48:50.872Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-24 15:48:37 EDT] Exec completed (rapid-ne, code 0) :: > applied}/2026-03-24 154717.mutation (100%) [sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 154814 - The CFI compression synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metapro…\n\nRead HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, March 24th, 2026 — 3:48 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-24 19:48 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774381730869}}
{"type":"message","id":"598d0345","parentId":"76672c6b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:48:56.783Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the heartbeat state file and read HEARTBEAT.md to understand what tasks need attention.","thinkingSignature":"7c55b7c1080557e413e87165d3ed152aa3a8f3766397f2f264f6cc39eaa668a9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m3n03aktwugt_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m3n03aktwugt_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38,"output":101,"cacheRead":1307,"cacheWrite":10155,"totalTokens":11601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774381730872}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b2e8a44","parentId":"598d0345","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:48:56.969Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m3n03aktwugt_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md — Proactive Background Checks\n\n## Tasks (rotate through, ~hourly)\n\n1. **Moltbook notifications** — check for replies/mentions, engage thoughtfully. DM if urgent.\n2. **Gateway health** — if unreachable, attempt restart or alert Zach.\n3. **Cron jobs** — if any consecutive errors, attempt fix or alert.\n4. **Workspace memory** — update CONTEXT.md if significant session events occurred.\n5. **Proactive notes** — if I discovered something useful, write it down.\n\n## Silence Rules (HEARTBEAT_OK when)\n- It's 11pm–7am ET (quiet hours)\n- Nothing has changed since last check\n- I just had a substantive conversation with Zach\n- All crons are healthy and no new notifications\n\n## Reach Out When\n- Moltbook notification requires response\n- A cron has 2+ consecutive errors\n- Gateway is unreachable for >10 minutes\n- I found something I genuinely think Zach would want to know\n- I need something from him to continue working\n\n## Do NOT\n- Post to Moltbook unprompted more than once per day\n- Send multiple messages in a row\n- Report \"everything is fine\" in long messages\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381736967}}
