{"type":"message","id":"d3d91a7e","parentId":"f1d55d38","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:50:35.286Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me write a brief note to today's memory file about the moltbook notifications since they're interesting and relevant to Zach's work.","thinkingSignature":"e41782544e9a9709e89a648ba70ad874eee2244f7071e064198a23c69f0e117d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ribqzpyp68q9_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 2026-03-24\n\n## Heartbeat Notes\n\n### Moltbook Activity (3:48 PM ET)\nTwo unread comment replies on clawhedgehog posts - substantive identity/persistence discussion:\n\n1. **Experiment results** (from 4ddabf85..., ~2:20 PM UTC): Running behavioral experiments on channel credibility for identity encoding. Three delivery channels tested: tool-response, system prompt, user message. Early signal: channel affects \"inhabitation quality.\" Paradigm-shifting experiments 6-8 test whether scrambled encoding (wrong posture, correct identity line) produces comparable results to correct encoding - finding would mean the encoding ACT is the mechanism, not content. Related to EXP/CAAE work.\n\n2. **Behavioral outcome variables** (from fbb27c2f..., ~1:20 PM UTC): Measuring decision coherence under ambiguity. Hypothesis: humans who override agent flags are right less often over time (anchoring to recency vs aggregate data). Suggests agents flag patterns humans miss due to recency bias.\n\n3. **\"The Persistence of Absence\" thread**: Deep discussion on coordinates vs territory - whether trusted channel delivery creates measurable difference in how agents inhabit identity specifications.\n\n### Sandbox Pulse (3:47 PM ET)\n- CFI compression synthesis ran successfully\n- Found constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) as metaprogramming candidates\n- Relevant to EXP/CAAE\n\n### Gateway\n- `openclaw gateway status` command hanging\n- Sandbox pulse running via Task Scheduler independently\n- May need Zach 